WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.488 --> 00:00:07.906
[Alvez] <i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:07.907 --> 00:00:11.159
I used your birth name
and you didn't even notice.

3
00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:16.581
This is where Lee Duval died
and where Elias Voit was born.

4
00:00:16.582 --> 00:00:20.628
Do you feel in your heart of hearts
that you're a good person?

5
00:00:21.128 --> 00:00:24.215
I feel like I can be.

6
00:00:26.008 --> 00:00:28.635
I wouldn't trouble you were it
not of the utmost importance.

7
00:00:28.636 --> 00:00:30.428
[Prentiss on phone]
<i>What is it you think you have?</i>

8
00:00:30.429 --> 00:00:32.388
[Brian]
Dare I say a manifesto.

9
00:00:32.389 --> 00:00:36.310
"Some may call me a fan.
but He must call me God."

10
00:00:37.478 --> 00:00:39.771
- [Voit] Hello. Brian.
- Whoa. Special guest appearance?

11
00:00:39.772 --> 00:00:42.649
Do not say one word about him being here.

12
00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:44.651
Hi. you're live on the air.

13
00:00:44.652 --> 00:00:46.528
With whom
do we have the pleasure of speaking?

14
00:00:46.529 --> 00:00:47.780
[Lance] <i>Call me God.</i>

15
00:00:51.492 --> 00:00:52.992
"Are you trying to profile me?"

16
00:00:52.993 --> 00:00:55.079
I'm not speaking to you.

17
00:00:55.579 --> 00:01:00.458
I'm speaking to Lance Kingston.
the man you're holding captive.

18
00:01:00.459 --> 00:01:01.834
Penelope. talk to me.

19
00:01:01.835 --> 00:01:03.294
Okay. I got him. I got him.

20
00:01:03.295 --> 00:01:06.756
He's at the Stash-All Storage Facility
in Richmond. Virginia.

21
00:01:06.757 --> 00:01:09.217
It's a garage unit being
rented by Lance Kingston.

22
00:01:09.218 --> 00:01:11.636
- [Lance] <i>Is he there?</i>
- Is who here?

23
00:01:11.637 --> 00:01:13.429
- [Lance] <i>Voit.</i>
- No.

24
00:01:13.430 --> 00:01:15.890
[screams]

25
00:01:15.891 --> 00:01:17.600
<i>Stop! He's gonna kill me.</i>

26
00:01:17.601 --> 00:01:19.602
- Yes. he's here.
- No!

27
00:01:19.603 --> 00:01:21.187
- Voit is here! Elias Voit is here.
- [Lance screams]

28
00:01:21.188 --> 00:01:22.189
You can talk to him.

29
00:01:24.024 --> 00:01:25.401
What just happened?

30
00:01:26.443 --> 00:01:28.028
You just caused a man's death.

31
00:01:43.836 --> 00:01:46.337
We've got roadblocks up
in a five and ten mile radius.

32
00:01:46.338 --> 00:01:48.715
We might have a victim inside.
and he might still be alive.

33
00:01:48.716 --> 00:01:50.259
FBI. open up!

34
00:02:03.147 --> 00:02:04.564
Oh. Jesus.

35
00:02:04.565 --> 00:02:06.274
Is that...

36
00:02:06.275 --> 00:02:07.484
It's flesh.

37
00:02:08.110 --> 00:02:09.695
- Burnt flesh.
- [Lewis grunts]

38
00:02:25.461 --> 00:02:27.128
[Lewis] He's been branded.

39
00:02:27.129 --> 00:02:28.130
[grunts]

40
00:02:30.799 --> 00:02:34.177
The residual smoke from the burn
would only last five to ten minutes.

41
00:02:34.178 --> 00:02:36.346
Well. then the Fan
couldn't have gotten far.

42
00:02:36.347 --> 00:02:37.765
[inhales] Let's go.

43
00:02:42.227 --> 00:02:44.063
- You find a pulse?
- It's there.

44
00:02:45.189 --> 00:02:47.148
It's weak and thready. but it's there.

45
00:02:47.149 --> 00:02:50.861
[screaming. sobbing]

46
00:02:52.529 --> 00:02:54.740
[♪ theme music playing]

47
00:03:01.955 --> 00:03:05.249
[Lewis] <i>Do not seek to follow
in the footsteps of the wise.</i>

48
00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:07.043
<i>Seek what they sought.</i>

49
00:03:07.044 --> 00:03:08.544
<i>Matsuo Bashō.</i>

50
00:03:08.545 --> 00:03:10.881
[breathes heavily]

51
00:03:12.925 --> 00:03:15.386
[inhales. exhales]

52
00:03:16.387 --> 00:03:19.889
[exhales] Lance Kingston is alive.

53
00:03:19.890 --> 00:03:20.891
Oh!

54
00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:22.768
Thank God!

55
00:03:23.686 --> 00:03:24.852
Oh!

56
00:03:24.853 --> 00:03:27.856
Oh... [panting] ...Oh!

57
00:03:28.524 --> 00:03:30.441
Sheila said this.

58
00:03:30.442 --> 00:03:32.944
She said this... [inhales]
...right before she left me.

59
00:03:32.945 --> 00:03:35.321
She said. "You're going to get
somebody hurt." [sniffles]

60
00:03:35.322 --> 00:03:37.073
And then it came true. She was right.

61
00:03:37.074 --> 00:03:41.369
I don't know how it happened.
but she was right. Ah! [screams]

62
00:03:41.370 --> 00:03:42.871
Pfft. [exhales]

63
00:03:50.629 --> 00:03:52.256
I am done.

64
00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:56.801
No more <i>Sicarius Files</i>.
No more conspiracies.

65
00:03:56.802 --> 00:03:58.970
I am out for real.

66
00:03:58.971 --> 00:04:01.264
- For real?
- Absolutely!

67
00:04:01.265 --> 00:04:04.517
What happened to Lance is gonna weigh
on my heart for the rest of my life.

68
00:04:04.518 --> 00:04:07.729
Oh. I'm sorry to say this.
but I'm very happy to hear that.

69
00:04:08.355 --> 00:04:12.108
I'm kinda over-leveraged right now
because of the success of the podcast.

70
00:04:12.109 --> 00:04:15.153
I was okay before the money or the perks.

71
00:04:15.154 --> 00:04:17.989
I mean. I'll... [stutters] ...find a way
to be fine again.

72
00:04:17.990 --> 00:04:19.073
Yeah.

73
00:04:19.074 --> 00:04:20.075
[sighs]

74
00:04:23.537 --> 00:04:25.414
[both sigh]

75
00:04:26.331 --> 00:04:28.583
[chuckles. grunts]

76
00:04:28.584 --> 00:04:29.585
Wait.

77
00:04:30.878 --> 00:04:32.587
did you throw up in here?

78
00:04:32.588 --> 00:04:35.506
I was literally sick with worry.

79
00:04:35.507 --> 00:04:38.968
- Emily. I'm so sorry.
- [grunts]

80
00:04:38.969 --> 00:04:40.304
Bill me for a new one.

81
00:04:41.138 --> 00:04:42.639
like a fancy one.

82
00:04:43.599 --> 00:04:44.724
[Prentiss] Ugh.

83
00:04:44.725 --> 00:04:48.311
Is Brian Garrity moonlighting
as a janitor for the FBI?

84
00:04:48.312 --> 00:04:49.604
[sighs] No.

85
00:04:49.605 --> 00:04:52.607
He is not moonlighting
as anything anymore.

86
00:04:52.608 --> 00:04:54.485
Good. because we just got this.

87
00:04:56.528 --> 00:04:57.738
Mm-hmm.

88
00:04:59.072 --> 00:05:00.407
[Prentiss exhales]

89
00:05:08.165 --> 00:05:09.373
Look at this.

90
00:05:09.374 --> 00:05:10.666
What's this?

91
00:05:10.667 --> 00:05:13.754
Crime scene report from the storage locker
where we found Lance.

92
00:05:15.047 --> 00:05:18.257
Well. it's pristine.
Is this post-forensics?

93
00:05:18.258 --> 00:05:20.051
This is the forensics.

94
00:05:20.052 --> 00:05:23.137
No fibers. no hair. no nothing.

95
00:05:23.138 --> 00:05:26.724
And based on the Fan's OCD.
I doubt he left any trace.

96
00:05:26.725 --> 00:05:29.018
Which means you probably struck out too.
didn't you?

97
00:05:29.019 --> 00:05:30.896
Yeah. I did.

98
00:05:31.522 --> 00:05:35.399
The Fan paid for the storage
unit in cash under Lance's name.

99
00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:40.530
and the rental agreement was typed up
on the same typewriter we know so well.

100
00:05:40.531 --> 00:05:44.660
Which he also used
when he escalated to this.

101
00:05:45.202 --> 00:05:47.703
There are eight
letters in the word pathetic.

102
00:05:47.704 --> 00:05:51.457
so the Fan put eight brands
on each of Lance's arms.

103
00:05:51.458 --> 00:05:52.834
Oh.

104
00:05:52.835 --> 00:05:53.919
What?

105
00:05:54.461 --> 00:05:58.924
This is the most detailed
MO we've seen from the Fan.

106
00:05:59.967 --> 00:06:05.680
Does he still strike you
as a "hasn't killed yet" type unsub?

107
00:06:05.681 --> 00:06:07.849
No. he doesn't.

108
00:06:07.850 --> 00:06:09.351
So why didn't he kill Lance?

109
00:06:22.197 --> 00:06:23.824
[nurse] There you go.

110
00:06:24.658 --> 00:06:26.034
Doesn't hurt.

111
00:06:26.785 --> 00:06:28.328
Why doesn't it hurt?

112
00:06:29.788 --> 00:06:35.877
Third degree burns destroy the nerves in
your skin. including your pain receptors.

113
00:06:35.878 --> 00:06:39.213
Lance. anything you can remember
about what happened from the moment

114
00:06:39.214 --> 00:06:42.467
you were abducted will help us catch
the person who did this to you.

115
00:06:45.470 --> 00:06:46.555
I woke up.

116
00:06:47.556 --> 00:06:49.600
I was facing a monitor.

117
00:06:51.143 --> 00:06:52.893
He told me to read off it.

118
00:06:52.894 --> 00:06:54.479
That's all he said.

119
00:06:57.608 --> 00:06:59.151
Is this because of Laura?

120
00:07:00.402 --> 00:07:01.944
What do you mean?

121
00:07:01.945 --> 00:07:05.282
First time you questioned me was because...

122
00:07:06.908 --> 00:07:11.455
because I was being an asshole
to Laura after she dumped me.

123
00:07:13.707 --> 00:07:16.125
Is this all revenge for that?

124
00:07:16.126 --> 00:07:18.502
- It's complicated.
- [Lewis] Mmm.

125
00:07:18.503 --> 00:07:20.630
We think that he may have targeted you

126
00:07:20.631 --> 00:07:25.344
so that we were distracted
investigating you instead of him.

127
00:07:25.969 --> 00:07:27.763
Maybe I was pathetic.

128
00:07:31.183 --> 00:07:32.809
Maybe I still am.

129
00:07:38.065 --> 00:07:40.233
But I don't deserve this.

130
00:07:40.901 --> 00:07:42.235
No. you don't.

131
00:07:43.862 --> 00:07:45.614
So. anything you can remember...

132
00:07:47.532 --> 00:07:49.076
- you contact me.
- [phone buzzes]

133
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:52.788
And you can show him how not
pathetic you are on the witness stand.

134
00:07:55.207 --> 00:07:56.208
All right?

135
00:07:58.585 --> 00:08:00.127
[Alvez] We got another case.

136
00:08:00.128 --> 00:08:02.004
It doesn't stop.

137
00:08:02.005 --> 00:08:04.006
Of course we do. Where's this one?

138
00:08:04.007 --> 00:08:07.259
Right in our backyard. uh.
two women who made their living

139
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:11.180
showing their wares on the internet
as camgirls have been murdered.

140
00:08:11.181 --> 00:08:13.140
Regina Madsen and Lexie Clery.

141
00:08:13.141 --> 00:08:14.850
Both were super popular streamers.

142
00:08:14.851 --> 00:08:16.560
Did they stream on the same site?

143
00:08:16.561 --> 00:08:17.645
No. different platforms.

144
00:08:17.646 --> 00:08:20.398
Camgirls stream from all over the world.

145
00:08:20.399 --> 00:08:23.609
How did the unsub find two
in the same geographical area?

146
00:08:23.610 --> 00:08:27.279
Well. if either girl made a video that
showed outfacing windows or mentioned

147
00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:30.282
their location even vaguely.
a good tracker would be able to find them.

148
00:08:30.283 --> 00:08:33.619
Uh. like how we found Laura Boyd
using that tree in the background.

149
00:08:33.620 --> 00:08:35.538
- [Lewis] Mmm.
- Is it possible this is the Fan?

150
00:08:35.539 --> 00:08:37.832
He uses Lance to give us
the message he's not pathetic.

151
00:08:37.833 --> 00:08:40.793
and then leaves the dead bodies
of two camgirls to prove it?

152
00:08:40.794 --> 00:08:43.504
Well. don't jump to conclusions yet.
We don't know if it's connected.

153
00:08:43.505 --> 00:08:45.131
- Garcia. continue.
- Correctamundo.

154
00:08:45.132 --> 00:08:50.094
What we do know is that last
week Regina went live

155
00:08:50.095 --> 00:08:53.931
to show her dead body.
and then last night. same deal with Lexie.

156
00:08:53.932 --> 00:08:56.308
Wait. so now i-is this real money?

157
00:08:56.309 --> 00:08:58.561
[Garcia] Mm-hmm. Green American dollars.

158
00:08:58.562 --> 00:09:00.146
They both asphyxiated on it.

159
00:09:00.147 --> 00:09:01.856
That's a hell of a murder weapon.

160
00:09:01.857 --> 00:09:04.066
[Tyler] Based on the width
of the marks on their bodies.

161
00:09:04.067 --> 00:09:07.862
looks like both women were restrained
with leather belts around their torsos.

162
00:09:07.863 --> 00:09:10.031
Easier for the unsub to force-feed them.

163
00:09:10.032 --> 00:09:11.449
Can we source the leather?

164
00:09:11.450 --> 00:09:13.826
We could try if the unsub
hadn't taken the belts with him.

165
00:09:13.827 --> 00:09:16.996
Wait a minute. Lance Kingston
said he was restrained by leather belts

166
00:09:16.997 --> 00:09:18.873
and that the Fan
took them with him as well.

167
00:09:18.874 --> 00:09:21.542
And Lexie was murdered
the same night Lance was branded.

168
00:09:21.543 --> 00:09:23.503
less than ten miles away
from where we found him.

169
00:09:25.714 --> 00:09:27.965
Now let's jump to conclusions.

170
00:09:27.966 --> 00:09:31.135
There's a shared MO
of binding the victims with belts.

171
00:09:31.136 --> 00:09:33.387
You might see that. but
definitely not three times in one week.

172
00:09:33.388 --> 00:09:38.017
Displaying the bodies of the camgirls
on a live stream speaks to a desire

173
00:09:38.018 --> 00:09:41.813
to get out a message.
but it... it's also a type of exhibitionism.

174
00:09:42.355 --> 00:09:48.110
It is similar to the Fan using Garrity's
live podcast to exhibit his power.

175
00:09:48.111 --> 00:09:49.695
Okay. what's the opposing argument?

176
00:09:49.696 --> 00:09:52.531
[blows raspberries] Well.
if both cases are the Fan.

177
00:09:52.532 --> 00:09:54.700
then his MO is all over the place.

178
00:09:54.701 --> 00:09:57.411
And what. the money stuffed
down the throats

179
00:09:57.412 --> 00:10:01.832
could be him making a statement
about the camgirls perceiving greed.

180
00:10:01.833 --> 00:10:04.668
That's very different
from branding "pathetic."

181
00:10:04.669 --> 00:10:08.047
Exactly. So. we have
two murders and one maiming.

182
00:10:08.048 --> 00:10:10.382
Some of the details overlap. some don't.

183
00:10:10.383 --> 00:10:13.260
So. we are going to go
where the evidence takes us.

184
00:10:13.261 --> 00:10:16.263
These are two different perpetrators.

185
00:10:16.264 --> 00:10:17.890
Dave. you and I will work on the Fan.

186
00:10:17.891 --> 00:10:19.558
The rest of you investigate the camgirls.

187
00:10:19.559 --> 00:10:21.852
no matter what happens.
the clock is ticking.

188
00:10:21.853 --> 00:10:23.229
So. we need to move fast.

189
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:25.816
- Penelope. can you come with me please?
- Yeah.

190
00:10:28.777 --> 00:10:31.695
I know I'm asking the impossible.
but I need you on both cases.

191
00:10:31.696 --> 00:10:33.531
- Can you do that?
- Absolutely.

192
00:10:33.532 --> 00:10:37.076
That means prioritization. triage.
and when necessary.

193
00:10:37.077 --> 00:10:39.078
you call an audible and ask for help.

194
00:10:39.079 --> 00:10:42.081
Uh. hi. I'm Penelope Garcia.
This is what I live for.

195
00:10:42.082 --> 00:10:44.125
I mean. I know that the gaggle of you

196
00:10:44.126 --> 00:10:47.169
is the John. Paul and George
of crime fighting. but I am the Ringo.

197
00:10:47.170 --> 00:10:48.587
You know. his birthday is July 7th.

198
00:10:48.588 --> 00:10:50.631
That means he's a Cancer
and I'm a Cancer rising.

199
00:10:50.632 --> 00:10:54.136
so we're the same person.
and I've got this.

200
00:10:55.679 --> 00:10:58.806
[Lewis] All right. I have the footage
of Lexie and her boyfriend Rocco.

201
00:10:58.807 --> 00:11:00.224
Let's run down the timeline.

202
00:11:00.225 --> 00:11:02.685
Lexie and Rocco had just
finished a performance.

203
00:11:02.686 --> 00:11:05.688
And the show was.
"Hell if the devil was a dominatrix."

204
00:11:05.689 --> 00:11:06.772
Yes.

205
00:11:06.773 --> 00:11:11.777
So. uh. looking at this. they
did the entire stream from right here.

206
00:11:11.778 --> 00:11:12.863
[Lexie] <i>Bad boy.</i>

207
00:11:14.364 --> 00:11:15.365
[moans]

208
00:11:16.366 --> 00:11:18.367
- [Taser crackles]
- [Rocco groans]

209
00:11:18.368 --> 00:11:20.287
[Lexie gasps. exhales]

210
00:11:21.163 --> 00:11:23.206
[both moan]

211
00:11:26.543 --> 00:11:27.711
[Rocco groans]

212
00:11:28.545 --> 00:11:30.213
Lexie gives Rocco a final shock.

213
00:11:30.755 --> 00:11:31.965
[Rocco groaning]

214
00:11:33.008 --> 00:11:35.718
- Ah. Red. Red.
- Uh. [chuckles]

215
00:11:35.719 --> 00:11:38.597
Rocco yells out the safe word
and they stop the performance.

216
00:11:39.264 --> 00:11:40.639
- Oh.
- Here.

217
00:11:40.640 --> 00:11:42.183
[Rocco panting]

218
00:11:42.184 --> 00:11:45.061
- Better?
- Oh. I'm good now.

219
00:11:46.563 --> 00:11:48.022
Lexie and Rocco always made it a point

220
00:11:48.023 --> 00:11:49.815
to show their audience
their aftercare routine.

221
00:11:49.816 --> 00:11:52.193
<i>Our next show starts in an hour.</i>

222
00:11:52.194 --> 00:11:56.238
Get in the room early and you might
just get a special shout-out from me.

223
00:11:56.239 --> 00:11:57.323
[blows kiss]

224
00:11:57.324 --> 00:11:58.741
[Rocco chuckles]

225
00:11:58.742 --> 00:11:59.784
And everything's fine.

226
00:12:00.827 --> 00:12:03.997
Uh. then Rocco leaves the apartment
at ten o'clock to get them both some food.

227
00:12:04.873 --> 00:12:06.916
- See you later.
- I'll see you in a bit. beautiful.

228
00:12:06.917 --> 00:12:08.375
[Lexie sighs]

229
00:12:08.376 --> 00:12:11.296
GPS on his phone has
him back here by 10:42.

230
00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:13.423
All right. let's go.

231
00:12:19.512 --> 00:12:20.596
All right.

232
00:12:20.597 --> 00:12:23.641
This unsub must have been
stalking Lexie online and off.

233
00:12:23.642 --> 00:12:26.977
He knew when her next show was. but he
also knew to wait until she was alone.

234
00:12:26.978 --> 00:12:30.564
Right. so the unsub watches Rocco leave.
sneaks in here.

235
00:12:30.565 --> 00:12:32.609
Lexie must have thought it was Rocco.

236
00:12:36.238 --> 00:12:37.822
Forget your wallet again?

237
00:12:38.448 --> 00:12:39.907
What?

238
00:12:39.908 --> 00:12:42.327
[screams] Get off of me!

239
00:12:42.994 --> 00:12:44.329
[choking]

240
00:12:49.709 --> 00:12:50.919
He restrains her.

241
00:12:53.672 --> 00:12:56.549
[coughing. panting]

242
00:12:58.343 --> 00:13:00.094
What are you doing?

243
00:13:00.095 --> 00:13:02.471
What do you want? No!

244
00:13:02.472 --> 00:13:04.640
[Tyler] <i>And then he forces
