- [door opens]

477
00:24:12.468 --> 00:24:14.386
Have I got an update for you.

478
00:24:14.387 --> 00:24:17.097
- Do you see that. that right there?
- The exclamation point.

479
00:24:17.098 --> 00:24:22.185
That is not supposed to exist
because typewriters made before 1960s

480
00:24:22.186 --> 00:24:23.855
didn't have a one key.

481
00:24:24.939 --> 00:24:26.940
- Wait.
- No. she's right.

482
00:24:26.941 --> 00:24:30.277
I remember you would use the lowercase L.

483
00:24:30.278 --> 00:24:34.948
So. if there's no one.
there's no exclamation point either.

484
00:24:34.949 --> 00:24:39.411
Well. did the Fan get a special
plate for just one punctuation mark?

485
00:24:39.412 --> 00:24:43.123
I don't think so.
I think he used a period and an apostrophe

486
00:24:43.124 --> 00:24:46.251
and made his own exclamation plate.

487
00:24:46.252 --> 00:24:48.712
Which means he didn't
use any modern typewriter.

488
00:24:48.713 --> 00:24:52.174
And older typewriters have very limited.
you know. variety of typefaces

489
00:24:52.175 --> 00:24:54.926
which narrows down where he's getting
his building materials from.

490
00:24:54.927 --> 00:24:58.263
Not to mention the larger font. that
should make it easier to find as well.

491
00:24:58.264 --> 00:25:01.850
Mm-hmm. And even if he had
a large font typewriter.

492
00:25:01.851 --> 00:25:05.562
he'd still need to get another striker
because pathetic has two T's.

493
00:25:05.563 --> 00:25:07.856
- [clicks tongue]
- [Rossi] What's the point of all that?

494
00:25:07.857 --> 00:25:09.525
Just to call us pathetic?

495
00:25:10.151 --> 00:25:11.736
Might not be for us.

496
00:25:13.779 --> 00:25:14.906
Right.

497
00:25:16.407 --> 00:25:19.285
Right. Let's go see him.

498
00:25:22.914 --> 00:25:24.456
- Is he...
- Don't worry about him.

499
00:25:24.457 --> 00:25:25.957
What about you...

500
00:25:25.958 --> 00:25:28.585
Is that the same
outfit you wore yesterday?

501
00:25:28.586 --> 00:25:30.462
Did you go to bed last night?

502
00:25:30.463 --> 00:25:32.172
Yeah. I som...

503
00:25:32.173 --> 00:25:35.426
I don't... I'm fine.
Why do I have to change every day?

504
00:25:36.385 --> 00:25:38.429
[announcer on PA] <i>Inmates. clear the tier.</i>

505
00:25:39.388 --> 00:25:41.264
Well. he's not Mark David Chapman.

506
00:25:41.265 --> 00:25:42.682
[Prentiss] No. he's not.

507
00:25:42.683 --> 00:25:43.934
What is he then?

508
00:25:43.935 --> 00:25:45.603
A copycat of you.

509
00:25:46.395 --> 00:25:47.896
I never branded anyone.

510
00:25:47.897 --> 00:25:50.441
Ever restrained anyone
with a leather belt?

511
00:25:52.944 --> 00:25:54.778
There are three kinds of copycats.

512
00:25:54.779 --> 00:25:59.366
One who wants to learn everything
he can about the killer he's emulating.

513
00:25:59.367 --> 00:26:02.077
One who wants everyone
to think that his crimes

514
00:26:02.078 --> 00:26:04.829
are being committed
by the killer he's emulating.

515
00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:06.039
And then there's the third.

516
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:09.125
the one who wants to be
better than his predecessor.

517
00:26:09.126 --> 00:26:10.628
Like Derek Brown. You remember him?

518
00:26:11.963 --> 00:26:14.005
Yeah. He copied Jack the Ripper.

519
00:26:14.006 --> 00:26:16.007
but they never found
the bodies of his two victims.

520
00:26:16.008 --> 00:26:18.344
so he was almost better
until they caught him.

521
00:26:20.263 --> 00:26:22.807
Studied that case
after you wrote a book about it.

522
00:26:23.808 --> 00:26:24.892
Exactly.

523
00:26:27.103 --> 00:26:29.813
Ah. I see what you're saying.

524
00:26:29.814 --> 00:26:32.566
It's almost like I'm a copycat of you.
right. Dave?

525
00:26:36.654 --> 00:26:42.075
We think the Fan is like Brown.
or the school shooter model

526
00:26:42.076 --> 00:26:46.079
inspired by the Columbine shooters.
only he's trying to surpass you.

527
00:26:46.080 --> 00:26:48.456
So. he's doing everything I did
before I started killing.

528
00:26:48.457 --> 00:26:52.586
but now he feels advanced enough
to do his own thing.

529
00:26:53.754 --> 00:26:55.797
which means it's probably isn't his first.

530
00:26:55.798 --> 00:26:57.341
That's what we thought.

531
00:26:57.925 --> 00:26:59.135
Who do you think it is?

532
00:27:02.263 --> 00:27:03.389
I don't know.

533
00:27:05.599 --> 00:27:06.726
You know.

534
00:27:09.145 --> 00:27:11.022
- No. I don't know...
- You know.

535
00:27:13.649 --> 00:27:16.193
And you've already done something.
haven't you?

536
00:27:17.653 --> 00:27:18.654
Dave.

537
00:27:19.905 --> 00:27:21.573
you said yourself.
I've grown a conscience.

538
00:27:21.574 --> 00:27:23.743
I wouldn't do anything
to jeopardize your trust.

539
00:27:26.871 --> 00:27:27.913
Yeah.

540
00:27:29.206 --> 00:27:32.168
You've studied me and I've studied you.

541
00:27:34.879 --> 00:27:39.800
So. whatever you did.
I will figure it out.

542
00:27:55.649 --> 00:27:56.650
[Brian] No.

543
00:27:57.359 --> 00:27:59.820
Yeah. all the information was in the ad.

544
00:28:01.322 --> 00:28:04.115
No. I'm not gonna drop
the price on the podcast notes.

545
00:28:04.116 --> 00:28:06.868
Do you have any idea what's in there?
Do you understand?

546
00:28:06.869 --> 00:28:08.496
They should be in the Smithsonian.

547
00:28:09.997 --> 00:28:12.791
The price is non-negotiable.

548
00:28:12.792 --> 00:28:16.419
No. I'm not gonna
throw in the podcast sign.

549
00:28:16.420 --> 00:28:18.923
Because someone's on the way
right now to buy it.

550
00:28:19.924 --> 00:28:22.759
- Okay. you listen to me. you little shit.
- [knocks on door]

551
00:28:22.760 --> 00:28:25.429
Oh. All right.
here's what I can do for you.

552
00:28:32.478 --> 00:28:33.729
Hey. Brian.

553
00:28:34.647 --> 00:28:35.730
Sheila.

554
00:28:35.731 --> 00:28:37.232
Can I come in?

555
00:28:37.233 --> 00:28:40.193
Oh... [chuckles] ...yeah. sure.

556
00:28:40.194 --> 00:28:42.946
- I wasn't expecting you.
- [both chuckle]

557
00:28:42.947 --> 00:28:45.365
- You look fantastic.
- Aw.

558
00:28:45.366 --> 00:28:47.408
- I didn't mean...
- No. no. It's okay.

559
00:28:47.409 --> 00:28:50.995
Listen. after the divorce. I could
