you're gonna narc on me?

604
00:31:09.426 --> 00:31:12.011
- Excuse me. I need to tell you something.
- Jesus Christ. Okay.

605
00:31:12.012 --> 00:31:14.890
Okay. look. I had to get you a message
so that you would come and see me.

606
00:31:19.687 --> 00:31:22.022
I just wanted to say
thank you for your service.

607
00:31:27.027 --> 00:31:29.195
Well. wives are off-limits.

608
00:31:29.196 --> 00:31:32.657
Wives. children. exes.
estranged or otherwise.

609
00:31:32.658 --> 00:31:34.909
don't act like you don't know
how this works all of a sudden.

610
00:31:34.910 --> 00:31:36.620
Do you wanna hear my message?

611
00:31:38.289 --> 00:31:39.539
Okay.

612
00:31:39.540 --> 00:31:42.792
I too know what it's like
to lose the person whose respect

613
00:31:42.793 --> 00:31:44.711
you want more than anything in the world.

614
00:31:44.712 --> 00:31:48.841
I too know what it's like to want to do
anything to look better in their eyes.

615
00:31:49.383 --> 00:31:51.343
And I know how you can do that.

616
00:31:52.594 --> 00:31:53.886
What are you talking about?

617
00:31:53.887 --> 00:31:55.889
She got hooked on the podcast. didn't she?

618
00:31:56.473 --> 00:31:59.809
I wouldn't say hooked.
She was impressed. but anyway.

619
00:31:59.810 --> 00:32:02.020
it doesn't matter
because the podcast is over.

620
00:32:02.021 --> 00:32:03.271
Well. what if it's not?

621
00:32:03.272 --> 00:32:05.357
I have another message for the Fan.

622
00:32:06.025 --> 00:32:09.528
On an SD card recorded on the same phone
I used to call your ex-wife.

623
00:32:10.696 --> 00:32:12.238
Give it to the BAU.

624
00:32:12.239 --> 00:32:14.198
Yeah. they have a tendency
to screw shit up.

625
00:32:14.199 --> 00:32:17.660
You screwed shit up
when you insulted the Fan.

626
00:32:17.661 --> 00:32:19.579
You're right. I did.

627
00:32:19.580 --> 00:32:21.205
I tried to control the story.

628
00:32:21.206 --> 00:32:22.957
I tried to control
what people thought of me.

629
00:32:22.958 --> 00:32:26.003
but I only made things worse
because it's not my story anymore.

630
00:32:27.046 --> 00:32:28.047
It's yours.

631
00:32:31.175 --> 00:32:32.343
Can I tell you what I think?

632
00:32:33.510 --> 00:32:34.511
Please.

633
00:32:36.388 --> 00:32:40.850
I think you see me
as an easily manipulatable patsy.

634
00:32:40.851 --> 00:32:45.104
someone you can get to do
your bidding with a little ego boost

635
00:32:45.105 --> 00:32:47.023
or if that doesn't work.
you throw in a little.

636
00:32:47.024 --> 00:32:51.028
"Oh. Brian. we're not so different.
you and I." Am I close?

637
00:32:55.532 --> 00:32:57.284
Well. let me tell you something.

638
00:32:57.993 --> 00:33:00.871
And this is coming from a very real place.

639
00:33:05.417 --> 00:33:08.545
You and I are very different.

640
00:33:10.464 --> 00:33:11.465
Mmm.

641
00:33:13.133 --> 00:33:15.969
Well. do you even know
what that difference is?

642
00:33:19.181 --> 00:33:21.933
There is
a burgeoning serial killer out there

643
00:33:21.934 --> 00:33:23.935
who I'm pretty sure
has already killed once

644
00:33:23.936 --> 00:33:26.104
but is in a bit of a cooling off period.

645
00:33:26.105 --> 00:33:27.481
And why do you think that is?

646
00:33:28.774 --> 00:33:32.111
What has happened to distract
him to stop him from escalating?

647
00:33:33.570 --> 00:33:34.821
My show.

648
00:33:34.822 --> 00:33:37.533
And that is
the difference between you and me.

649
00:33:38.784 --> 00:33:40.576
I can't stop him from in here.

650
00:33:40.577 --> 00:33:43.288
The BAU can't stop him from anywhere but...

651
00:33:45.582 --> 00:33:47.126
you can.

652
00:33:53.549 --> 00:33:55.509
Thank you for coming to see me.

653
00:34:19.970 --> 00:34:21.887
Wow. What's all this?

654
00:34:21.888 --> 00:34:25.308
Uh. Garcia got all the online chats
Percy had with paying customers.

655
00:34:27.644 --> 00:34:30.063
[chuckles] "Until the room stinks."

656
00:34:32.607 --> 00:34:35.359
I don't know why I'm reading it out loud.
I'm sorry.

657
00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:40.406
Yes. uh... [huffs] ...so way more than half
of these are much older gentlemen.

658
00:34:40.407 --> 00:34:43.909
Yeah. it looks like Percy was
real popular with the AARP army.

659
00:34:43.910 --> 00:34:46.245
Okay. so could our unsub be an older man?

660
00:34:46.246 --> 00:34:49.415
That would explain why
1976 means so much to him.

661
00:34:49.416 --> 00:34:51.500
That could be when his lovemap was formed.

662
00:34:51.501 --> 00:34:52.668
[Lewis] Well. that tracks.

663
00:34:52.669 --> 00:34:55.088
All of our victims
made videos in a '70s persona.

664
00:34:55.714 --> 00:34:58.007
These chats all mentioned food.

665
00:34:58.008 --> 00:35:01.427
So. I looked through some of Regina's
older videos from the time of the chats.

666
00:35:01.428 --> 00:35:05.097
She did a series of mukbangs
with some very regional foods.

667
00:35:05.098 --> 00:35:06.682
What's a mukbang?

668
00:35:06.683 --> 00:35:11.103
Oh. It is when someone eats
an insane amount of food on camera.

669
00:35:11.104 --> 00:35:13.188
I cannot tell you why.
but they are incredibly popular.

670
00:35:13.189 --> 00:35:15.941
[Tyler] So popular
that Lexie did one as well.

671
00:35:15.942 --> 00:35:17.610
Regina had a ton of blue crabs.

672
00:35:17.611 --> 00:35:20.946
Lexie finished hers
with a big box of Berger cookies.

673
00:35:20.947 --> 00:35:23.116
Yeah. we're talking incredibly regional.

674
00:35:23.867 --> 00:35:27.202
Without saying where they lived. these
women still ended up exposing themselves.

675
00:35:27.203 --> 00:35:28.746
- Yeah.
- [Alvez] Mmm.

676
00:35:28.747 --> 00:35:30.706
Solves your geo-profile problem.

677
00:35:30.707 --> 00:35:33.709
Yeah. it's part
of his parasocial delusion.

678
00:35:33.710 --> 00:35:36.253
He wants to believe
these women were his peers.

679
00:35:36.254 --> 00:35:39.131
They grew up in the old neighborhood.
Remember how good it was.

680
00:35:39.132 --> 00:35:41.635
And then when
the relationship soured. he killed them.

681
00:35:43.053 --> 00:35:45.930
We need to comb all of
our victims' communications.

682
00:35:45.931 --> 00:35:48.557
I mean. any mention of regional food
could be our unsub.

683
00:35:48.558 --> 00:35:51.810
Okay. we are gonna have to come back
and help you read through these.

684
00:35:51.811 --> 00:35:54.606
We gotta get to the ME.
They finished Percy's autopsy.

685
00:35:55.357 --> 00:35:56.942
- Sorry.
- [Lewis] Mmm.

686
00:35:57.984 --> 00:35:59.319
Oh. come on.

687
00:36:01.321 --> 00:36:03.989
He put coins inside Percy?

688
00:36:03.990 --> 00:36:07.701
Not only did he use coins this time.
his total was changed.

689
00:36:07.702 --> 00:36:09.954
I took all the cash from Percy's
mouth and stomach.

690
00:36:09.955 --> 00:36:12.581
and then I found two dimes
deep in his bowels.

691
00:36:12.582 --> 00:36:15.919
bringing the grand total to $395.20.

692
00:36:16.753 --> 00:36:23.050
Wait. that's... that's exactly
20% of Lexie and Regina's amounts.

693
00:36:23.051 --> 00:36:25.177
- [chuckles]
- What?

694
00:36:25.178 --> 00:36:28.597
I got good at mental math
from playing darts.

695
00:36:28.598 --> 00:36:31.308
I needed a calculator... [chuckles]
...but you're right.

696
00:36:31.309 --> 00:36:34.186
I looked for more coins and bills in case
I was missing something.

697
00:36:34.187 --> 00:36:35.647
but that's all I found.

698
00:36:36.231 --> 00:36:38.565
I called you in so fast
because I was worried there might be

699
00:36:38.566 --> 00:36:41.193
four other victims making up
the rest of the money somewhere.

700
00:36:41.194 --> 00:36:43.113
I-I don't think it's that.

701
00:36:43.989 --> 00:36:47.032
We thought 1976 was about a date.

702
00:36:47.033 --> 00:36:49.910
but if he's willing to make a 20% cut

703
00:36:49.911 --> 00:36:52.913
for the guy who took 20%
of the camgirls' earnings.

704
00:36:52.914 --> 00:36:54.873
he's saying something else.

705
00:36:54.874 --> 00:36:56.000
Like what?

706
00:36:56.001 --> 00:36:57.292
[JJ] Not sure.

707
00:36:57.293 --> 00:37:01.631
Sometimes a cigar is a cigar.
maybe the money is just about the money.

708
00:37:07.095 --> 00:37:08.595
I spoke with forensics.

709
00:37:08.596 --> 00:37:12.307
The brands on Lance Kingston's body
are all the same depth.

710
00:37:12.308 --> 00:37:15.769
meaning all the letters are
the same brand of typewriter.

711
00:37:15.770 --> 00:37:17.897
Penelope.
you said you had something on that.

712
00:37:20.358 --> 00:37:22.109
[snoring]

713
00:37:22.110 --> 00:37:23.987
Penelope. hey.

714
